This paper proposes a proof-of-work algorithm for blockchain mining that involves solving NP-complete puzzles, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the decentralized nature of the proposed blockchain, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of NP-complete problems for proof-of-work also relates to the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential real-world applications of the solutions generated by the blockchain, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the security of the proposed blockchain, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
